WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:14.916
Hello.
大家好。

2
00:00:14.940 --> 00:00:16.140
My name is Simone.
我是Simone。

3
00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:20.396
You know how people tell you if you get nervous when onstage,
人们总是告诉你 当你在舞台上感到紧张的时候，

4
00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:22.916
picture people in the audience naked?
假想观众都没穿衣服就好了。

5
00:00:22.940 --> 00:00:26.316
Like it's this thing that's supposed to make you feel better.
说的就像这真能让你感觉好点一样。

6
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:27.596
But I was thinking --
但是我一直在想——

7
00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:33.036
picturing all of you naked in 2018 feels kind of weird and wrong.
在2018年想象你们都没穿衣服 实在有点不太对啊。

8
00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:36.076
Like, we're working really hard on moving past stuff like that,
我们都有在努力克服这样的问题，

9
00:00:36.100 --> 00:00:38.716
so we need a new method of dealing with
所以我们需要一种新方法，

10
00:00:37.940 --> 00:00:40.830
if you get nervous onstage.
来应付舞台恐惧症。

11
00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:43.036
And I realized that what I'd really like
我意识到，我真正想要的是

12
00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:47.116
is that I can look at you as much as you're looking at me --
我能跟你们看着我一样看着你们，

13
00:00:47.140 --> 00:00:49.556
just to even things out a little bit.
只是为了公平一点。

14
00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:52.316
So if I had way more eyeballs,
所以如果我有更多眼睛的话，

15
00:00:52.340 --> 00:00:55.116
then we'd all be really comfortable, right?
那我们就都会很舒服，对吧？

16
00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:58.876
So in preparation for this talk, I made myself a shirt.
所以为了准备这次演讲 我给自己做了件T恤。

17
00:00:58.930 --> 00:01:02.050
(Rattling)
（窸窸窣窣的声音）

18
00:01:04.820 --> 00:01:06.740
(Laughter)
（笑声）

19
00:01:09.620 --> 00:01:12.596
It's googly eyes.
这就是大眼睛T恤。

20
00:01:12.620 --> 00:01:14.716
It took me 14 hours
花了我14个小时，

21
00:01:14.740 --> 00:01:18.436
and 227 googly eyes to make this shirt.
以及227个大眼睛贴片。

22
00:01:18.460 --> 00:01:21.516
And being able to look at you as much as you're looking at me
能够像你们看着我一样 看着你们这件事，

23
00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:24.036
is actually only half of the reason I made this.
其实只是我制作 这件T恤的部分原因。

24
00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:25.996
The other half is being able to do this.
另一半原因是我可以这么玩儿。

25
00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:27.356
(Googly eyes rattle)
（大眼睛T恤的响声）

26
00:01:27.380 --> 00:01:28.636
(Laughter)
（笑声）

27
00:01:28.660 --> 00:01:30.396
So I do a lot of things like this.
我做过很多这样的事。

28
00:01:30.420 --> 00:01:34.236
I see a problem and I invent some sort of solution to it.
我发现了一个问题， 就会发明某个解决方法来应对它。

29
00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:36.076
For example, brushing your teeth.
比如刷牙这件事：

30
00:01:36.100 --> 00:01:39.036
Like, it's this thing we all have to do, it's kind of boring,
这就是一件大家都得做， 但是又有点无聊的事，

31
00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:41.156
and nobody really likes it.
而且没人真正喜欢刷牙。

32
00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:43.556
If there were any seven-year-olds in the audience,
如果在座有7岁小朋友的话，

33
00:01:43.580 --> 00:01:46.076
they'd be like, "Yes!"
他们肯定会大喊“就是这样！”

34
00:01:46.100 --> 00:01:48.940
So what about if you had a machine that could do it for you?
那么要不要来一台 自动帮你刷牙的机器呢？

35
00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:57.740
(Laughter)
（笑声）

36
00:01:58.540 --> 00:01:59.780
I call it ...
我给它取了名，

37
00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:04.140
I call it "The Toothbrush Helmet."
叫做“牙刷头盔”。

38
00:02:04.820 --> 00:02:07.500
(Laughter)
（笑声）

39
00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:12.036
(Robot arm buzzing)
（机器人的手臂声）

40
00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:15.276
(Laughter)
（笑声）

41
00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:18.796
(Applause)
（掌声）

42
00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:23.356
So my toothbrush helmet is recommended by zero out of 10 dentists,
10位牙医中，有0位 推荐了我的牙刷头盔，

43
00:02:23.380 --> 00:02:27.556
and it definitely did not revolutionize the world of dentistry,
它也肯定不算颠覆 牙医界的伟大发明，

44
00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:30.756
but it did completely change my life.
但它确实改变了我的生活。

45
00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:34.236
Because I finished making this toothbrush helmet three years ago
因为3年前我做出了这个头盔，

46
00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:35.796
and after I finished making it,
完成制作之后，

47
00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:38.476
I went into my living room and I put up a camera,
我在客厅架起了摄像机，

48
00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:40.980
and I filmed a seven-second clip of it working.
录了一个7秒长的头盔操作视频。

49
00:02:41.580 --> 00:02:42.796
And by now,
现在，

50
00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:45.716
this is a pretty standard modern-day fairy tale
这成了一个标准的现代版童话：

51
00:02:45.740 --> 00:02:47.956
of girl posting on the internet,
一个女孩在网上发帖，

52
00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:50.556
the internet takes the girl by storm,
跟上了互联网浪潮，

53
00:02:50.580 --> 00:02:53.396
thousands of men voyage into the comment sections
数以千计的男人们涌进评论区，

54
00:02:53.420 --> 00:02:55.116
to ask for her hand in marriage --
邀请她进入婚姻殿堂——

55
00:02:55.140 --> 00:02:56.156
(Laughter)
（笑声）

56
00:02:55.830 --> 00:02:58.460
She ignores all of them, starts a YouTube channel
而她无视了他们所有人， 创立了一个YouTube频道，

57
00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:00.180
and keeps on building robots.
继续搭建机器人。

58
00:03:00.940 --> 00:03:04.876
Since then, I've carved out this little niche for myself on the internet
从那时起我在互联网上为自己 发掘出了这么一个商机：

59
00:03:04.900 --> 00:03:07.396
as an inventor of useless machines,
无用机器发明者。

60
00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:09.076
because as we all know,
因为大家都知道，

61
00:03:09.100 --> 00:03:12.756
the easiest way to be at the top of your field
成为你所在行业顶尖人物的 最简单方法，

62
00:03:12.780 --> 00:03:14.876
is to choose a very small field.
就是选择一个非常小的行业。

63
00:03:14.900 --> 00:03:17.116
(Laughter)
（笑声）

64
00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:21.476
(Applause)
（鼓掌）

65
00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:24.676
So I run a YouTube channel about my machines,
所以我在运营一个 关于我的机器的YouTube频道，

66
00:03:24.700 --> 00:03:27.476
and I've done things like cutting hair with drones --
我有试过用无人机剪头发——

67
00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:29.196
(Drone buzzes)
（无人机噪声）

68
00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:31.596
(Laughter)
（笑声）

69
00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:32.676
(Drone crashes)
（无人机坠毁）

70
00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.116
(Laughter)
（笑声）

71
00:03:34.140 --> 00:03:35.236
(Drone buzzes)
（无人机噪声）

72
00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:37.156
(Laughter)
（笑声）

73
00:03:37.180 --> 00:03:39.276
(Applause)
（掌声）

74
00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:42.036
To a machine that helps me wake up in the morning --
我还做过一台闹钟机器——

75
00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:43.996
(Alarm)
（闹铃声）

76
00:03:43.980 --> 00:03:46.420
(Laughter)
（笑声）

77
00:03:49.020 --> 00:03:50.756
(Video) Simone: Ow!
（视频）Simone：噢！

78
00:03:50.780 --> 00:03:53.356
To this machine that helps me chop vegetables.
还有这台帮我切菜的机器。

79
00:03:53.380 --> 00:03:55.820
(Knives chop)
（切菜声）

80
00:03:57.020 --> 00:03:58.276
I'm not an engineer.
我不是个工程师，

81
00:03:58.300 --> 00:04:00.636
I did not study engineering in school.
我没学过工程学，

82
00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:04.236
But I was a super ambitious student growing up.
但我从小就是个 特别有远大志向的学生。

83
00:04:04.260 --> 00:04:06.756
In middle school and high school, I had straight A's,
无论初中高中我一路拿的都是A，

84
00:04:06.780 --> 00:04:08.996
and I graduated at the top of my year.
而且我毕业那年还是名列前茅的。

85
00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:10.276
On the flip side of that,
但另一面是，

86
00:04:10.300 --> 00:04:13.996
I struggled with very severe performance anxiety.
我当时有非常严重的表现焦虑。

87
00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:17.066
Here's an email I sent to my brother around that time.
这是一封当时我写给我兄弟的邮件。

88
00:04:17.060 --> 00:04:19.956
"You won't understand how difficult it is for me to tell you,
“你不会明白， 光是告诉你这件事，

89
00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:21.196
to confess this.
对我来说有多难。

90
00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:22.596
I'm so freaking embarrassed.
实在是太难堪了。

91
00:04:22.620 --> 00:04:24.836
I don't want people to think that I'm stupid.
我不希望人们觉得我是个傻子。

92
00:04:24.860 --> 00:04:26.436
Now I'm starting to cry too.
我现在居然还开始哭了。

93
00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:27.916
Damn."
真讨厌。”

94
00:04:27.940 --> 00:04:31.476
And no, I did not accidentally burn our parents' house down.
别误会，我可没有不小心 把爸妈的房子烧了。

95
00:04:31.500 --> 00:04:35.796
The thing I'm writing about in the email and the thing I'm so upset about
信里面那件让我 如此焦虑不安的事其实是，

96
00:04:35.820 --> 00:04:38.060
is that I got a B on a math test.
有一次数学测验我只拿了B。

97
00:04:39.300 --> 00:04:42.500
So something obviously happened between here and here.
所以这两种情况之间 一定发生了什么事情。

98
00:04:43.420 --> 00:04:47.836
(Laughter)
（笑声）

99
00:04:47.860 --> 00:04:50.036
One of those things was puberty.
其中一件是青春期的到来。

100
00:04:50.060 --> 00:04:51.436
(Laughter)
（笑声）

101
00:04:51.460 --> 00:04:52.836
Beautiful time indeed.
非常美丽的时期。

102
00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:54.196
But moreover,
但除此之外，

103
00:04:54.220 --> 00:04:56.356
I got interested in building robots,
我开始对搭建机器人感兴趣，

104
00:04:56.380 --> 00:04:59.636
and I wanted to teach myself about hardware.
我还想自学硬件知识。

105
00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:03.156
But building things with hardware, especially if you're teaching yourself,
但搭建需要硬件的东西， 尤其是当你是在自学的时候，

106
00:05:02.936 --> 00:05:05.586
is something that's really difficult to do.
是一件非常困难的事情。

107
00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:07.476
It has a high likelihood of failure
失败几率非常高，

108
00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:08.716
and moreover,
并且，

109
00:05:08.740 --> 00:05:11.516
it has a high likelihood of making you feel stupid.
这很有可能让你 觉得自己超级智障。

110
00:05:11.540 --> 00:05:13.660
And that was my biggest fear at the time.
而那就是我当时最大的恐惧。

111
00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:20.716
So I came up with a setup that would guarantee success 100 percent of the time.
所以我做了一个一定能 保证100%成功率的设定。

112
00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:24.116
With my setup, it would be nearly impossible to fail.
根据我的设定， 失败可能性几乎为零。

113
00:05:24.140 --> 00:05:27.116
And that was that instead of trying to succeed,
我打算再试着获得成功，

114
00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:29.700
I was going to try to build things that would fail.
我要制作一个肯定失败的机器。

115
00:05:31.180 --> 00:05:33.436
And even though I didn't realize it at the time,
尽管我当时并没有意识到，

116
00:05:33.460 --> 00:05:37.396
building stupid things was actually quite smart,
但实际上，制作一无是处东西 其实还是个挺聪明的点子。

117
00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:40.076
because as I kept on learning about hardware,
因为当我对硬件的学习 更加深入的时候，

118
00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:41.556
for the first time in my life,
我人生中第一次，

119
00:05:41.580 --> 00:05:44.100
I did not have to deal with my performance anxiety.
不用应对自我表现方面的焦虑。

120
00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:48.396
And as soon as I removed all pressure and expectations from myself,
并且当我卸除了所有 对自己的压力与期待后，

121
00:05:48.420 --> 00:05:51.796
that pressure quickly got replaced by enthusiasm,
压力很快就被热情取代，

122
00:05:51.820 --> 00:05:53.580
and it allowed me to just play.
我就可以只是瞎玩了。

123
00:05:54.700 --> 00:05:55.956
So as an inventor,
所以，作为一个发明者，

124
00:05:55.980 --> 00:05:58.396
I'm interested in things that people struggle with.
我对人们很难做到的事情很感兴趣。

125
00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:01.996
It can be small things or big things or medium-sized things
可以是小事，大事， 或者二者之间的事。

126
00:06:02.020 --> 00:06:06.556
and something like giving a TED talk presents this whole new set of problems
而做一场TED演讲， 带来了一系列我能解决的

127
00:06:06.580 --> 00:06:08.076
that I can solve.
全新问题。

128
00:06:08.100 --> 00:06:11.196
And identifying a problem is the first step in my process
而发现问题则是搭建

129
00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:12.700
of building a useless machine.
一个无用机器的第一步。

130
00:06:13.340 --> 00:06:14.876
So before I came here,
在我来这里之前，

131
00:06:14.900 --> 00:06:18.476
I sat down and I thought of some of the potential problems I might have
我坐下来好好思考了一番演讲时

132
00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:19.780
in giving this talk.
可能遇到的问题：

133
00:06:20.540 --> 00:06:21.820
Forgetting what to say.
忘词，

134
00:06:23.300 --> 00:06:24.596
That people won't laugh --
没人笑——

135
00:06:24.620 --> 00:06:25.820
that's you.
说的就是你哦。

136
00:06:26.900 --> 00:06:28.116
Or even worse,
或者更糟的是，

137
00:06:27.966 --> 00:06:30.060
that you'll laugh at the wrong things --
你们笑错地方了，

138
00:06:31.300 --> 00:06:32.876
that was an OK part to laugh at,
这里你们其实是可以笑的，

139
00:06:32.900 --> 00:06:34.116
thank you.
谢谢。

140
00:06:33.626 --> 00:06:34.620
(Laughter)
（笑声）

141
00:06:34.620 --> 00:06:37.440
Or that when I get nervous, my hands start shaking
或者我一紧张就会手抖，

142
00:06:37.580 --> 00:06:39.636
and I'm really self-conscious about it.
我还非常清楚这一点。

143
00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:42.796
Or that my fly has been open this entire time
或者我的裤子拉链一直都没拉上，

144
00:06:42.820 --> 00:06:44.876
and all of you noticed but I didn't,
所有人都注意到了，就我没有。

145
00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:47.956
but it's closed so we're all good on that one.
但它是拉好的，所以没事了。

146
00:06:47.980 --> 00:06:51.436
But one thing I'm actually really nervous about is my hands shaking.
我最担心的就是手抖这个问题了。

147
00:06:51.460 --> 00:06:53.636
I remember when I was a kid,
我还记得我小时候

148
00:06:53.660 --> 00:06:55.356
giving presentations in school,
在学校做演讲时，

149
00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:57.476
I would have my notes on a piece of paper,
我会在一张纸上准备讲稿，

150
00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:00.956
and I would put a notebook behind the paper
并将纸贴到一个笔记本上，

151
00:07:00.980 --> 00:07:04.236
so that people wouldn't be able to see the paper quivering.
这样人们就看不出纸在颤抖了。

152
00:07:04.260 --> 00:07:05.980
And I give a lot of talks.
我做过很多演讲。

153
00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:10.876
I know that about half of you in the audience are probably like,
我知道你们中有一半听众 都可能这么想：

154
00:07:10.900 --> 00:07:12.876
"Building useless machines is really fun,
“制作无用机器确实挺好玩，

155
00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:15.556
but how is this in any way or form a business?"
但这怎么可能是商机呢？”

156
00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:17.516
And giving talks is a part of it.
演讲就是其中的一部分，

157
00:07:17.540 --> 00:07:20.596
And the arrangers always put out a glass of water for you onstage
组织者一定会在讲台上 给你放杯水，

158
00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:22.956
so you have something to drink if you get thirsty,
这样你渴的时候就有水喝了。

159
00:07:22.980 --> 00:07:26.876
and I always so badly want to drink that water,
我每次都超级想喝那杯水，

160
00:07:26.900 --> 00:07:28.756
but I don't dare to pick the glass up
但我没有勇气拿起杯子，

161
00:07:28.780 --> 00:07:32.076
because then people might be able to see that my hands are shaking.
因为人们可能就看出我的手在抖。

162
00:07:32.100 --> 00:07:36.196
So what about a machine that hands you a glass of water?
那么要不要来一台 递给你一杯水的机器呢？

163
00:07:36.220 --> 00:07:39.396
Sold to the nervous girl in the googly-eye shirt.
就卖给穿大眼睛T恤的 那位紧张女孩！

164
00:07:39.420 --> 00:07:42.420
Actually, I need to take this off because I have a thing --
实际上我得把这T恤脱了， 因为我有个玩意儿要展示——

165
00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:46.140
(Googly eyes rattle)
（大眼睛们窸窸窣窣）

166
00:07:51.220 --> 00:07:52.636
Oh.
噢

167
00:07:52.660 --> 00:07:54.156
(Clanking)
（叮当声）

168
00:07:54.180 --> 00:07:56.940
(Laughter)
（笑声）

169
00:08:05.300 --> 00:08:08.276
I still don't know what to call this,
我还是不知道给它起什么名字。

170
00:08:08.300 --> 00:08:11.836
but I think some sort of "head orbit device,"
就叫“头部环绕仪”之类的吧。

171
00:08:11.860 --> 00:08:14.876
because it rotates this platform around you
因为这个平台会绕着你的头旋转，

172
00:08:14.900 --> 00:08:16.396
and you can put anything on it.
