00:09:14.020 --> 00:09:15.940
but I think we're all good.
但应该没事儿。

198
00:09:17.060 --> 00:09:19.476
OK, also I need to chew this popcorn,
好的， 我先把爆米花咽下去，

199
00:09:19.500 --> 00:09:22.436
so if you guys could just clap your hands a little bit more --
所以你们再鼓一会掌好了。

200
00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:26.556
(Applause)
（掌声）

201
00:09:26.580 --> 00:09:29.396
OK, so it's like your own little personal solar system,
这就像个私人迷你太阳系，

202
00:09:29.420 --> 00:09:31.316
because I'm a millennial,
因为我是千禧一代，

203
00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:33.796
so I want everything to revolve around me.
所以我希望所有东西都围着我转。

204
00:09:33.820 --> 00:09:36.876
(Laughter)
（笑声）

205
00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:39.516
Back to the glass of water, that's what we're here for.
回到那杯水的问题， 那是我们来到这里的原因。

206
00:09:39.540 --> 00:09:41.596
So, I promise -- I mean, it still has --
我保证，它里头还有——

207
00:09:41.620 --> 00:09:43.196
it doesn't have any water in it,
这杯子里面没有水，

208
00:09:43.220 --> 00:09:44.716
I'm sorry.
抱歉。

209
00:09:44.740 --> 00:09:49.316
But I still need to work on this machine a little bit
但我还得调整一下这个机器，

210
00:09:49.340 --> 00:09:52.596
because I still need to pick up the glass and put it on the platform,
因为我还是得 拿起杯子放到平台上，

211
00:09:52.620 --> 00:09:54.636
but if your hands are shaking a little bit,
但如果你的手在抖，

212
00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:55.916
nobody's going to notice
没有人能注意到了，

213
00:09:55.940 --> 00:09:58.836
because you're wearing a very mesmerizing piece of equipment.
因为你身上正穿着一台 很迷人的机器呢。

214
00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:00.276
So, we're all good.
目前为止一切正常。

215
00:10:00.300 --> 00:10:01.500
OK.
很好。

216
00:10:01.966 --> 00:10:03.116
(Robot buzzes)
（机器声）

217
00:10:03.140 --> 00:10:04.580
(Singing)
（歌声）

218
00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:08.116
Oh no, it got stuck.
哦不，它卡住了。

219
00:10:08.140 --> 00:10:11.300
Isn't it comforting that even robots sometimes get stage fright?
连机器都会犯舞台恐惧症， 是不是很让人放松啊？

220
00:10:12.020 --> 00:10:13.860
It just gets stuck a little bit.
它只是有一点点卡住 。

221
00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:16.780
It's very human of them.
非常人性化哦。

222
00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:20.316
Oh wait, let's go back a little bit,
等一下，我们倒回去一点。

223
00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:21.556
and then --
然后——

224
00:10:21.580 --> 00:10:22.796
(Glass falls)
（玻璃杯触地声）

225
00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:24.996
(Laughter)
（笑声）

226
00:10:25.020 --> 00:10:27.476
Isn't it a beautiful time to be alive?
活在这个时代真好，是吧？

227
00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:29.756
(Laughter)
（笑声）

228
00:10:29.780 --> 00:10:34.380
(Applause)
（掌声）

229
00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:41.116
So as much as my machines can seem like simple engineering slapstick,
我的机器看起来 像是在用工程学做简单的恶搞，

230
00:10:41.140 --> 00:10:44.556
I realize that I stumbled on something bigger than that.
但我意识到我触及到了 一些比这更重要的事。

231
00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:49.476
It's this expression of joy and humility that often gets lost in engineering,
制造机器时往往无法 表现得开心或谦逊。

232
00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:52.036
and for me it was a way to learn about hardware
对我而言，用这种方式学硬件，

233
00:10:52.060 --> 00:10:54.860
without having my performance anxiety get in the way.
是不会受到表现焦虑症干扰的。

234
00:10:55.860 --> 00:10:59.476
I often get asked if I think I'm ever going to build something useful,
经常有人问我，我以后会不会 制作一些有用的东西？

235
00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:01.020
and maybe someday I will.
可能有一天我会。

236
00:11:02.260 --> 00:11:03.556
But the way I see it,
但我觉得，

237
00:11:03.580 --> 00:11:04.876
I already have
我早已做到了。

238
00:11:04.900 --> 00:11:07.260
because I've built myself this job
这份工作是我为自己创造出的。

239
00:11:08.140 --> 00:11:10.996
and it's something that I could never have planned for,
这是我无法计划出来的。

240
00:11:11.020 --> 00:11:12.236
or that I could --
或者——

241
00:11:12.260 --> 00:11:16.380
(Applause)
（掌声）

242
00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:20.236
It's something that I could never have planned for.
这是我永远也无法计划出的。

243
00:11:20.260 --> 00:11:23.796
Instead it happened just because I was enthusiastic about what I was doing,
相反，这一切的发生 只是因为我对这个工作充满热情，

244
00:11:23.820 --> 00:11:26.556
and I was sharing that enthusiasm with other people.
并且我在与他人分享我的热情。

245
00:11:26.580 --> 00:11:29.956
To me that's the true beauty of making useless things,
对于我，那就是制作 无用机器最美的部分。

246
00:11:29.980 --> 00:11:31.996
because it's this acknowledgment
因为你已经承认，

247
00:11:32.020 --> 00:11:34.420
that you don't always know what the best answer is.
你不一定知道最好的答案是什么。

248
00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:37.316
And it turns off that voice in your head
它让你不再盲目认为 

249
00:11:37.340 --> 00:11:40.796
that tells you that you know exactly how the world works.
自己已经完全了解世界怎么运作。

250
00:11:40.820 --> 00:11:43.156
And maybe a toothbrush helmet isn't the answer,
可能一台牙刷头盔并不是标准答案，

251
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:45.116
but at least you're asking the question.
但至少你提出了问题。

252
00:11:45.140 --> 00:11:46.356
Thank you.
谢谢。

253
00:11:46.380 --> 00:11:50.420
(Applause)
（掌声）